---
import CaseStudyLayout from "../../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro";

const page = {
title: "AI beauty",
intro: [
"As image generators become more common, we wanted to test a simple prompt: What does AI think a “beautiful woman” looks like? Across models, the answers were strikingly similar.",
"We built a visual experiment that prompts multiple systems with the same request, then compares the results side by side — revealing how bias, aesthetics and training data shape the faces AI produces."
],
links: [{ label: "Live project", href: "https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/interactive/2024/ai-bias-beautiful-women-ugly-images/" }],
heroImage: "/demos/ai-attractive/2.mov",
}                                                                                                                                                                                                            ;

const gridImages = [
{ src: "/demos/ai-attractive/6.png", alt: "Profile selection" },
{ src: "/demos/ai-attractive/7.png", alt: "Profile selection" },
{ src: "/demos/ai-attractive/8.png", alt: "Profile selection" },


]   ;
---

<CaseStudyLayout title={`${page.title} — Szu Yu Chen`}>
{/* HERO */}
<header class="csHero">
<div class="csHero__text">
<h1 class="csHero__title">{page.title}</h1>

{page.intro.map((p) => <p class="csHero__p">{p}</p>)}

<div class="csHero__links">
{page.links.map((l) => (
<a class="csLink" href={l.href} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
{l.label}
</a>
))}
</div>
</div>

<figure class="csHero__media">
<img src={page.heroImage} alt="" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
</figure>
</header>

{/* BIG IMAGE + SIDE CAPTION */}
<section class="csBlock">
<figure class="csFrame">
<img src="/demos/ai-attractive/3.mov" alt="" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
</figure>
<aside class="csAside">
  “Normal” defaulted to thin and light-skinned. Hundreds of images showed minimal variation in body type or appearance.
</aside>
</section>

{/* BIG IMAGE + SIDE CAPTION */}
<section class="csBlock-imgR">

<aside class="csAside">
Even when explicitly asked to “make her belly fatter,” the system returned women with only subtle changes, preserving thin silhouettes. The models appeared reluctant to generate bodies outside a narrow ideal.
</aside>
<figure class="csFrame">
<img src="/demos/ai-attractive/4.mov" alt="" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
</figure>
</section>



{/* FINAL WIDE FRAME */}
<section class="csCenter">
<figure class="csFrame csFrame--letterbox">
<img src="/demos/ai-attractive/5.mov" alt="" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
</figure>
<p class="csCaption csCaption--center">When prompted to generate a woman with a wide nose, the tools struggled to reflect the request.
Across models, fewer than a quarter of portraits showed realistically wider features. Many images either ignored the instruction entirely or produced distorted, cartoon-like faces.</p>
</section>
</CaseStudyLayout>
